cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.ST, cs.IT, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a new dependency measure between a high dimensional random variable and a response variable, which can be used for nonlinear feature selection. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also uses sparsity inducing gradient penalties and presents a neural version of the proposed measure, which suggests that it may also belong to the statistics (cs.ST), information theory (cs.IT), or computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
